      "rationale": "The primary QOI (relative hemolysis index, RH) is directly mapped to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device) specified in the COU. Secondary QOIs (wall shear stress distribution, scalar stress exposure time) are clinically validated surrogates for erythrocyte damage. Traceability matrix linking each QOI to a specific COU decision requirement is documented and reviewed by clinical subject matter expert. QOI selection justified against FDA guidance on blood-contacting device testing."
