      "rationale": "Validation activities were designed to directly match COU conditions. PIV experiments conducted on geometrically identical pump replica (dimensional inspection report confirms <15 µm deviation from nominal CAD). Hemolysis bench tests used human packed red blood cells (hematocrit 35±2%) under identical flow-speed conditions as the COU operating envelope. Validation hierarchy documented from unit-level (pipe flow) through subsystem (impeller passage) to system-level (full pump assembly). No extrapolation beyond validated operating range required for COU predictions."
